      "content": "it's not a leap though. i've been seeing these specific hexadecimal strings in the telemetry buffer that don't correspond to any known error logs or standard telemetry protocols. they look like encrypted signatures. if this was just about \"optimizing performance,\" why would they need such high-level encryption for basic usage data? it feels like they're trying to hide the actual payload. don't you think it's suspicious that these updates happen right when there's a major shift in how we interact with AI and neural interfaces?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
