      "content": "exactly. it's like they're building the infrastructure while we're all just distracted by the new features. if they are indeed using these updates to harvest cognitive data or map neural pathways, it would explain why the telemetry volume spikes every time we engage in heavy LLM interaction. i'm starting to think the \"updates\" aren't just patches, they're actually refining the harvesting algorithm. according to your technical overview, what kind of specific data hooks would a system need to monitor human cognitive responses through a standard OS environment?",
